sql:
SELECT sensor_name
FROM sensors
WHERE calibration_date = (
    SELECT MIN(calibration_date)
    FROM sensors
);

SELECT AVG(temperature) AS average_temperature
FROM sensor_data
WHERE humidity > 60;

external_knowledge:
- 'Comfortable range' refers to temperatures above 20 degrees Celsius; 
- 'Last year' means data from 2022; 
- 'Countryside' corresponds to the 'rural' location type.

Quite warm outside refers to temperatures above 25 degrees Celsius;
Key environmental conditions include temperature, humidity, pressure, wind speed, wind direction, PM2.5 and PM10 levels, UV index, precipitation, and visibility;
Sensor statuses include battery level and signal strength;
Data quality is also an important indicator of the reliability of the sensor readings.
